  , issuePullRequest = Nothing
  , issueUrl =
      "https://api.github.com/repos/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/3032"
  , issueCreatedAt = 2014 (-09) (-11) 04 : 29 : 27 UTC
  , issueBody =
      Just
        "#2720 (modernized joins) will allow us to drop `r.zip`. We should redefine `zip` to do what you'd expect. Along with #875 (`r.range`) that would take care of #2574 (array iteration):\r\n\r\n```py\r\n# The simple case\r\n> r.expr([0, 1, 2, 3]).zip(['a', 'b', 'c', 'd'])\r\n[[0, 'a'], [1, 'b'], [2, 'c'], [3, 'd']]\r\n\r\n# Also, postfix notation\r\n> r.zip([0, 1, 2, 3], ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd'])\r\n[[0, 'a'], [1, 'b'], [2, 'c'], [3, 'd']]\r\n\r\n# Different length should behave same way as Python's `zip` does\r\n> r.expr([0, 1, 2]).zip(['a', 'b', 'c', 'd'])\r\n[[0, 'a'], [1, 'b'], [2, 'c']]\r\n\r\n> r.expr([0, 1, 2, 3]).zip(['a', 'b', 'c'])\r\n[[0, 'a'], [1, 'b'], [2, 'c']]\r\n\r\n# If anything's empty, we get an empty array\r\n> r.expr([0, 1, 2, 3]).zip([])\r\n[]\r\n\r\n> r.expr([]).zip(['a', 'b', 'c'])\r\n[]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen I could do:\r\n\r\n```py\r\n> r.zip(r.range(), ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd'])\r\n[[0, 'a'], [1, 'b'], [2, 'c'], [3, 'd']]\r\n```\r\n\r\n/cc @mlucy "
